President Trump gave a speech addressing the opioid crisis in Manchester, New Hampshire. He discussed the severity of the crisis and the need for strong action to combat it. Trump highlighted the importance of preventing addiction, reducing drug supply, and providing help to those in need. He also called for tougher penalties for drug dealers, including the possibility of the death penalty. Additionally, he mentioned efforts to lower drug prices and improve access to treatment. The President thanked individuals and companies that have taken steps to address the crisis, and emphasized the need for unity and determination in tackling the issue.